&lt;p&gt;Are you an experienced agronomist ready to make a difference in the Mallee, Wimmera, Riverina, SA and beyond? At Dodgshun Medlin, we&#39;re looking for a specialist like you to join our team. This role offers a unique opportunity for professional growth and personal satisfaction, as we focus on advising clients rather than sales.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;About Us&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dodgshun Medlin is a unique blend of agronomists, accountants, tax, finance, risk, and wealth specialists, all working together to create seamless planning for enterprise farming. Delivering foresight, clarity and confidence. Since our founding in 1957, we&#39;ve played a significant role in transforming the Mallee into a prosperous cropping region. With our base in Swan Hill, a Collins Street office, and a growing network of regional satellites, we&#39;re expanding our reach across VIC, SA and NSW. We&#39;re committed to sustainability, diversity, and the welfare of our communities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;About You&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for someone who:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Has a minimum of 5 years of experience as an agronomist&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Can monitor, identify, diagnose, and recommend suitable weed, pest, disease, and nutrition management strategies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Has strong organisational and time-management skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Can form trusting client relationships&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Is an Australian Citizen or Permanent Resident&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;The Role&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Broadacre Agronomist, your responsibilities will include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Providing expert agronomic advice to our broadacre farming clients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensuring timely and excellent delivery of our service cycle&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborating with our seasoned team of advisors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Engaging with the farming community through discussion groups, crop walks, and industry events&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Developing comprehensive weed control strategies and formulating tailored nutrition and fertiliser plans&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Promoting operational efficiencies and implementing best practices for soil health and weed control management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assisting clients with crop rotation planning and variety selection&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collecting and analysing paddock data to inform our agronomic advice and recommendations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Our Mission&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our goal is to develop thriving regional communities, supported by sustainable, confident, and prosperous farming businesses. We integrate agronomic and financial services into tailored, seamless planning. We&#39;re ethical, professional, hard-working, and empathetic, and we derive immense satisfaction from helping our clients achieve their goals. If this resonates with you, we need you on our team.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.dodgshunmedlin.com.au/careers?utm_source=greenhouse&amp;amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;amp;utm_campaign=people-like-us&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://www.dodgshunmedlin.com.au/assets/img/greenhouse/PeopleLikeUs_RGB_139.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;People like us need people like you&quot; width=&quot;139&quot; style=&quot;max-width: 100%;&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Are you a Chartered Accountant with over 3 years of experience in public practice and a passion for delivering high-quality compliance and improvement services? We&#39;re looking for a professional like you to join our diverse team at Dodgshun Medlin. Your expertise will be instrumental in providing timely and consistent services to our clients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;About Us&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dodgshun Medlin is a trusted guide in the rural enterprise and wealth strategies of farming and related industries across regional Australia. Our unique approach integrates all professional services specialties – accountancy, tax, business improvement, finance, risk, wealth improvement, and more – into a seamless whole. Our team of in-house agronomists and our deep understanding of the land and regional complexities set us apart in the sector. At Dodgshun Medlin, you can accelerate your career while enjoying the stability and purpose that comes with working in Swan Hill, a vibrant community on the Murray.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;About You&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You&#39;re a Chartered Accountant with a Bachelor of Business/Commerce or similar&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have over 3 years of experience in public practice&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You possess strong interpersonal communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have experience preparing financial statements and tax returns for small to medium enterprises&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;It would be a plus if you have:&amp;nbsp;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A primary production interest and/or experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with tax planning and strategy development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in Xero&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;The Role&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Chartered Accountant, you&#39;ll:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver financial statements, tax returns, activity statements, and interim financial statements for clients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop expertise in efficient tax strategies, preparing forecasts, reporting, and advice on business structures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Present financial performance to clients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review other team members&#39; financials providing feedback on quality and efficiency&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify potential opportunities that Dodgshun Medlin could be assisting the clients with&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support team training and mentoring, including transfer of technical skills and knowledge&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.dodgshunmedlin.com.au/careers?utm_source=greenhouse&amp;amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;amp;utm_campaign=people-like-us&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://www.dodgshunmedlin.com.au/assets/img/greenhouse/PeopleLikeUs_RGB_139.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;People like us need people like you&quot; width=&quot;139&quot; style=&quot;max-width: 100%;&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Are you a recent or soon-to-be graduate with a passion for agricultural accountancy? Do you crave a career that offers variety, challenge, and a fast-paced environment? If so, Dodgshun Medlin is looking for you. We&#39;re a leading name in agribusiness, and we&#39;re on the hunt for graduates like you to join our team in Swan Hill, Australia.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;About Us&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dodgshun Medlin is a trusted guide in the rural enterprise and wealth strategies of farming and related industries across regional Australia. Our unique approach integrates all professional services specialties – accountancy, tax, business improvement, finance, risk, wealth improvement, and more – into a seamless whole. Our team of in-house agronomists and our deep understanding of the land and regional complexities set us apart in the sector. At Dodgshun Medlin, you can accelerate your career while enjoying the stability and purpose that comes with working in Swan Hill, a vibrant community on the Murray.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;The Role&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here&#39;s what you can expect:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support towards CA qualification&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work in multi-disciplinary teams to develop holistic solutions&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Early face-to-face client interaction&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use of ultra-modern tech – we&#39;re digital innovators&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Opportunities for growth and pathways to Tax, Business Development, SMSF, Financial Planning&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A diverse, inclusive, and supportive workplace&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Genuine, appreciative clients&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An ethical business with a commitment to sustainability and community engagement&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.dodgshunmedlin.com.au/careers?utm_source=greenhouse&amp;amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;amp;utm_campaign=people-like-us&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://www.dodgshunmedlin.com.au/assets/img/greenhouse/PeopleLikeUs_RGB_139.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;People like us need people like you&quot; width=&quot;139&quot; style=&quot;max-width: 100%;&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Are you ready to make a difference in broadacre farming while learning from the industry&#39;s best? At Dodgshun Medlin, we&#39;re offering an opportunity for graduates like you to assist our clients in planning and executing their crop strategies from sowing to harvest. You&#39;ll have the chance to work in a team, choose a speciality, attend training events and access specialist support in areas like crop nutrition, rotation, weed control, machinery, tech, and operations.&lt;/p&gt;
